The paper deals with the problem of cross-media retrieval, specifically between images and text. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper proposes a new neural network architecture, which falls under the domain of machine learning (cs.LG).
